  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Social Stability through Border Communities&#x2019; Empowerment in Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is to promote state and human security and enhance social cohesion around targeted Guinea border communities by supporting law enforcement agencies and border communities to be more effective, accountable, and inclusive. More specifically, the approach aims to strengthen Guinea&#x2019;s national border and migration management capacities and, in turn, support the Government of Guinea&#x2019;s commitment to facilitate the orderly flow of people and goods across the borders and to while reinforcing border community stability, amid COVID-19. The project equally aims at reinforcing the capacities of cross border communities in rural areas through community based early warning conflict alert system and the cross-border collaboration alongside Guinea-Liberia and C&#xF4;te d&#x2019;Ivoire borders.</narrative>
  </description>
